. `GDeath                                                          `Ygame concept
`K- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
 `wWhen your character dies, you are reincarnated back at the Altar of the Temple
 of Midgaard. Your corpse is left behind in the room where you were killed,
 together with all of your equipment. Your gold stays with you. 

 Any spells which were affecting you are canceled by death.

 Following and groups are not affected by death.

 You lose experience points for dying. The amount you lose is half-way back to
 the beginning of your level. Thus if you have a bad day and die several times,
 the penalties won't clobber you.

 Corpses decay after time, and the objects inside corpses decay with them.
 Player corpses last *roughly* 30 hours of game time (10 minutes of real time).
 Only the player who died, or someone in the same group, can retrieve objects
 from a player's corpse.
~
0 RAISE EXPERIENCE LEVEL XP~
. `GLEVEL                                                                  `Yinfo
`GRAISE                                                               `Ycommand
`K- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
 `wYour character advances in power by gaining experience. The amount of xp
 needed to gain a level depends to a degree upon your race and class.

 You gain experience by:

    being part of a group that kills a monster

 You lose experience by:

    fleeing from combat
    recalling out of combat
    being the target of certain spells
    dying

 There is a small amount of random variation in the amount of xp you recieve 
 from killing a certian mobile, although it is fairly consistant.

 You may type LEVEL or LEVELS at any time in the game to get a listing of
 how much xp you need to reach the next 4 levels in the game.

 To raise a level, type RAISE when you have negative experience to your
 next level.
~
