0 TANK~
. `GTank                                                           `Ygame concept
`K- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
 `wThe tank is the enemy of your enemy (ie, who your enemy is attacking).
 In most cases this is you, however if you are in a group and one member
 attacks a mob, the mob will attack him back. Then, if you assist that
 group member, HE is still the tank, and HE still takes damage from the
 mobs attacks.  

 Use the %t prompt code to display the tank's current condition when 
 grouped, and you will know if he needs to be RESCUED. When you are 
 not grouped, %t will show your current status, or nothing if you are
 not fighting.
~
0 PROMPT PROMPTS~
. `GPROMPT <prompt>                                                        `Yinfo
`K- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
 `wPROMPT is used to configure your prompt (the information displayed while
 the system is awaiting input from you). You can include any text or color
 codes in your prompt, as well as the following codes which are replaced
 as indicated.

  %h - current hit points       %H - maximum hit points
  %m - current mana             %M - maximum mana
  %v - current move points      %V - maximum move points
  %t - current time (12hr)      %T - current time (24hr)
  %s - your status (e.g. "nasty wounds and scratches")
  %e - enemy status (as above)
  %l - tank status (as above) - See help tank
  %W - command wait status (e.g. from getting bashed, tripped, etc.)
  %r - new line
  %A - Act bits AFK,KILLER,THIEF,WIZI(immort only)
  %x - current xp		%X - xp left to level
  %# - current room vnum(immort only)

 Also, you may replace the %h, %m, and %v codes with the following, which
 will show the current value in red if the value is under 33% of max, 
 yellow if under 66% of max, and white if over 66%.

  %i - variable color current hit points
  %n - variable color current mana
  %w - variable color current movement

 There are two default prompts accessible using prompt default and 
 prompt combat. 
~
